latestIgtvVideos.title: Raksha Bandhan 2020, celebrated it a little differently this year!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Families of frontline workers have been going through immense stress during these testing times. A Frontliner’s fight is also their family’s. 🙏🏻
.
Police services have always been one of the most challenging and stressful services in India and with changing times it is becoming even more so.
.
It’s not just during the time of pandemic but on festivals when the families spend time with their loved ones, our brave hearts work away from their families to safeguard us. Policemen sacrifice not only their lives but also their family’s life for guarding the society against threats, and people should be aware of this! 
.
I am fortunate to witness the selfless service of my brother and all other frontline workers who are working day and night without worrying about their own health. The least anyone can do is to support and have gratitude towards them, now more than ever.It’s motivating for them when the community is behind them.
.
Honestly, as a family, it brightens our day to know of his well-being when he returns back from his duty everyday. Though he is miles away from us on his service. 
And this year is different since many of us won’t be able to celebrate rakhi in the physical presence of our brothers. So keeping in mind the spirit of Raksha Bandhan- a bond of protection, we decided to celebrate VIRTUAL RAKHI, besides a prayer for my brother who is a corona warrior. 
@amitnigamips 
.
@bubble_theblueeyedfrenchie 
.

Looking at a brighter future when going out will be as normal as it was! 🤞💓

.
MONDAY : Keeping it formal for the first day of the week at work 👩🏻‍💼
TUESDAY : Ditched those heels for a more comfortable, yet formal look for the day 👩🏻‍🏫
WEDNESDAY : Mid-week calls for some brighter color while I take those work calls.
THURSDAY : It’s already Friday on my mind 😜

FRIDAY : Date night ready! 🥂
